<!-- Project Overview Section -->

<section class="project-overview" id="project-overview">

    <div class="project-overview-content">

        <h1 style="text-align:center; font-size:4.5rem; margin-bottom:50px;">Project <span>overview</span></h1>

        <h2 class="heading">What I had <span>to do</span></h2><!--Description of project-->
        <p>
            For this project I had to had to create a fullstack web application using various new technologies to me.
            Therefore I learned quite a lot of new things that I found quite challenging but not impossible.
            <br /><br />
            For this project we had to create a bulletinboard where you can create, delete and retrieve bulletingboard posts.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading">What I <span>did</span></h2>
        <p>
            To create the web application I used Visual Studio Code. I then used HTML, CSS and angular for the front end and 
            then TypeScript and NodeJs for the functionality of the application as well as MongoDB for the database. I also 
            used Stack Overflow and youtube to help me and fix any problems I had. I then submitted my project using Microsoft Teams.
        </p>

        <h2 class="heading">Potential problems and <span>errors</span></h2>
        <p>
            These are a few problems that might occur:
            <ol style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-right:20px;">
                <li>This project is web based but the website is not published so you have to run it from Visual Studio Code.</li>
                <li>There are databases used and they hosted but my account might have been deleted because it was a school
                    one and I haven't used it for a while.
                </li>
                <li>
                    There might be a slight certificate problem or something so you might not be able to view it but you
                    can read the documentation for pictures and other information.
                </li>
            </ol>

        </p>

    </div>

</section>




